import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['start'] = pd.to_datetime(data['start'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    plt.hist(data['start'])
    plt.xlabel('Start Year')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of monarchs by their reign start year?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['end'] = pd.to_datetime(data['end'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    plt.hist(data['end'], bins='auto', edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('End Year')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of monarchs by their reign end year?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['start'] = pd.to_datetime(data['start'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data['end'] = pd.to_datetime(data['end'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data['reign_length'] = (data['end'] - data['start']).dt.days / 365

    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.boxplot(data['reign_length'])
    plt.xticks([1], ['Reign Length'])

    avg_reign_length = np.mean(data['reign_length'])
    plt.axhline(avg_reign_length, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average: {avg_reign_length:.2f}')
    plt.legend()

    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))

    plt.title('What is the average length of reign for monarchs in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    commonwealth_counts = data['commonwealth'].value_counts(normalize=True)
    labels = ['Not part of Commonwealth', 'Part of Commonwealth']
    
    plt.pie(commonwealth_counts, labels=labels, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the proportion of monarchs who were part of the Commonwealth?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
